args: I take it your grandmother did not\napprove your enrollment?
Yeah. She said I couldn't because of\nsomething about mana and towns.
What?! That sounds like horse plop!

Remember that we are dealing with an
elderly woman and her granddaughter
living in the forest. She likely has concerns
we aren't privy to.
She's raising Maribelle entirely on her\nown, after all.
You clearly want to go to school, yes?
Because all I know about this world\nis the forest!
I wouldn't have known anything about\nschools or uniforms if you hadn't told me.
And if I don't get out into the world,\nI'm never gonna learn about it.
That's no good! I'm an adult now!
Those are good, thoughtful reasons.\nPerhaps we should speak to your granny\nand see if she will change her mind.
I'm sure she has reasons for not wanting\nyou to go, but if we can address them,\nshe may change her mind.
Of course. Friends help each other out\nin times of trouble, right?
My my. So this is the Halidom, eh?
Good afternoon, ma'am. I am...\nWell, I guess you could say this\nis my castle.
Many thanks for helping to take care\nof my granddaughter, young man.\nNow then! Why am I here?
We wanted to talk to you about your\ngranddaughter's desire to go to school.
I'm afraid I don't much like the idea.\nIt's for her own good, you understand?
See, my little Maribelle is very\nsensitive to mana.

And I'm afraid these old bones are too
slow to rush to her aid if something
were to happen while she was at a
school in some village.
If she ever strays from the forest,\nthere will be nothing I can do for her.
But what if we support her in your place?
Yes. I'll make her lunch every day, for one.
And should the need arise, I will go to\npick her up and see her safely home.
And I'll...uh...hang out and eat a lot!\nWhich is a very underrated skill.
Dude, you're gonna scare the old lady!
Why would you go so far for her?
Everyone here is my friend, Granny!
But if I can go to school,\nI can make MORE friends!
And that'll help me be an adult!
I reckon you've gone and grown up right\nbefore my eyes and I haven't noticed.
Mayhap that's just the way with children.
And we want to help her grow by showing\nher the world.
Will you at least consider it?
Very well. So long as you're ready for the\nwork, I'll leave Maribelle in your care.
Thank you, Granny! And everyone else!
Now that you've come all this way, ma'am,\nwon't you please stay for tea?
Ah. Might you be Cleo, young sylvan?
How do you know my name?
I've known of you for a long time now.
Thank you for always baking such\nwonderful treats for Maribelle.
I'm truly relieved to learn what kind of\nfolk are watching over her now.
I've always felt uneasy for her future,\nwhat with knowing my spirit will return\nto the forest before hers.
As one of the beings who dwells in this\nforest, I'll be able to keep watching over\nher, but no longer extend a helping hand.
Still, while I grew up in isolation,\nshe's surrounded by friends.
Even if she leaves the forest and goes\nbeyond my reach, I know she'll be fine.
Something about your mana feels...\nWait, are you
Heh heh. I leave Maribelle in your care,\nchild of the forest.
And as a child of the forest, I will honor\nyour request. ...But even if I wasn't,\nI would do so anyway.
Because she is a dear friend to us all.
